<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="T" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Troth" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Troth,</orth> 1) truth: <cit><quote>to speak t.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.2.36" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 2, 36</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>to say the t. on't,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 4.5.198" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. IV, 5, 198</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I'll speak t.</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.274" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 5, 274</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) faith: <cit><quote>she conjures him . . . by holy human law and common t.</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 571" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 571</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>thou smotherest honesty, thou murderest t.</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 571" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 571</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>thou shalt not know the stained taste of violated t.</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 571" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 571</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>that strong-bonded oath that shall prefer and undertake my t.</quote> <bibl n="shak. lc 280" default="NO" valid="yes">Compl. 280</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>and not break my t.</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 1.1.66" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 1, 66</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>break faith and t.</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.143" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 143</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>virtue's office never breaks men's t.</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.350" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 350</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>two bosoms and one t.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.2.42" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 2, 42</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.2.42" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 2, 42</bibl> <cit><quote>one man holding t.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.92" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 92</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>violation of all faith and t. sworn to us,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.1.70" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A V, 1, 70</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>faith and t.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 4.5.168" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. IV, 5, 168</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>bid her alight and her t. plight,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 3.4.128" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 4, 128</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the loyallest husband that did e'er plight t.</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 1.1.96" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 1, 96</bibl></cit>. Used to express a slight oath: <cit><quote>t.!</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.4.154" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 4, 154</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.2.177" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 177</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 2.1.228" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 1, 228</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 3.2.59" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 59</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 2.1.220" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 1, 220</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 3.4.6" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 5.4.77" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 77</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.1.27" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 1, 27</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 2.3.34" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 II, 3, 34</bibl> <emph>(yes, t. and t.)</emph> etc. <cit><quote>good t.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.2.129" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 2, 129</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. h8 2.3.33" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 II, 3, 33</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.6.48" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 6, 48</bibl>. <cit><quote>in t.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.2.12" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 2, 12</bibl></cit> (Qq <emph>by my t.</emph>). <cit><quote>in good t.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 3.1.124" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 1, 124</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>o' my t.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.2.36" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 2, 36</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.1.144" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 1, 144</bibl>. Oftenest <cit><quote>by my t.:</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.1.199" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 1, 199</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.1.199" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 1, 199</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mm 4.3.163" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 3, 163</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 4.3.163" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 3, 163</bibl> <bibl n="shak. err 3.1.62" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. III, 1, 62</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 1.1.226" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado I, 1, 226</bibl>. 228 <cit><quote>(by my two faiths and --s).</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 2.1.19" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 19</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ado 2.1.19" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 19</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ado 2.3.77" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 77</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 2.3.77" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 77</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ado 3.4.9" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 3.4.9" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 9</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.230" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 230</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.1.131" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 1, 131</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.450" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 450</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 1.2.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 2, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.2.94" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 2, 94</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.2.303" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 303</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.1.192" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 192</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 5.1.12" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 3.2.3" default="NO" valid="yes">All's III, 2, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.3.55" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 3, 55</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.2.12" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 2, 12</bibl> (Ff <emph>in t.</emph>). <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.2.64" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C III, 2, 64</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 2.4.23" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 4, 23</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.7.43" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 7, 43</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 2.3.23" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 II, 3, 23</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 3.1.116" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 1, 116</bibl> etc.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>